A 61-year-old man will appear in court on Tuesday after he was arrested for allegedly raping an 11-year-old girl in Motetema outside Groblersdal in Limpopo. According to the police, the suspect attacked the girl while she was on her way to a spaza shop. Police spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe said, upon her arrival at home, the child reported her ordeal to her mother, who later informed the police. “The police reacted swiftly and the suspect was positively identified and arrested,” Ngoepe said. -TNA Reporter